    "title": "Managing a Shared Resource Using a Singleton"
  },
  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You use singletons to provide a globally accessible, shared instance of a class.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "You can create your own singletons as a way to provide a unified access point to",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "a resource or service that’s shared across an app, like an audio channel to play",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "sound effects or a network manager to make HTTP requests.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Create-a-Singleton",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Create a Singleton",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You create simple singletons using a static type property, which is guaranteed to",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "be lazily initialized only once, even when accessed across multiple threads simultaneously:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "class Singleton {",
            "    static let shared = Singleton()",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "If you need to perform additional setup beyond initialization, you can assign the",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "result of the invocation of a closure to the global constant:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "class Singleton {",
            "    static let shared: Singleton = {",
            "        let instance = Singleton()",
            "        // setup code",
            "        return instance",
            "    }()",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
